 111.50\u2013112.00, the pair broke decisively higher from 14 July onwards, posting a sequence of higher daily closes that has carried price roughly 250 pips from the base of that consolidation. Yesterday's daily candle closed at 114.22, marking the highest close in the 30-session window under review, and the current session has opened in line with that close, suggesting the market is in a consolidative mode rather than a reversal.\n\nThe structure story is one of a base-and-break pattern. The 111.20\u2013111.60 region absorbed selling pressure across multiple sessions through late June, with buyers consistently defending that area. The 30 June surge through 112.50 was the first meaningful signal that the balance of supply and demand was shifting, and the subsequent grind higher through the 112.85 prior reaction zone \u2014 which had previously acted as a ceiling \u2014 confirmed a structural shift. That level has since been left well behind, and the 113.20 and 113.95 prior reaction zones were each absorbed on the way up, the latter now functioning as a meaningful layer of structure support roughly 25 pips below the overnight low. The immediate overhead prior reaction zone near 114.33 is the level to watch; the session high of 114.40 briefly pierced it this morning before price pulled back, leaving a small wick and suggesting some residual supply in that vicinity.\n\nOn the hourly chart, the picture is orderly. Since the 114.30 area was tested during the Asian session, price has drifted back to consolidate in the 114.19\u2013114.25 range, with candles showing tight bodies and limited directional conviction. The H1 structure remains constructive \u2014 there are no lower highs of significance yet, and the 113.95 prior reaction zone sits as a meaningful floor beneath current price. A sustained hold above 114.10 on the hourly would keep the near-term read intact.\n\nThe key event today is the Australian employment data due at 21:30 UTC, comprising both Employment Change and Unemployment Rate, both flagged as high-impact. This release carries the potential to generate sharp directional movement in AUD pairs. A stronger-than-expected headline \u2014 particularly a robust employment change figure \u2014 could provide the catalyst to clear the 114.33 prior reaction zone with conviction. Conversely, a disappointing print would likely test the 113.95 support zone and potentially bring the 113.20 structure support back into the conversation.\n\nThe bullish read would come under pressure on a daily close back below 113.20, which would suggest the recovery from the June lows has stalled materially. A break and hold beneath 113.95 on the hourly would soften the near-term picture ahead of the data.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}